There is a gauge that is online now that is right at the 115 bridge. This is a better gauge to go<br/>
by because the Duncan Bridge gauge includes a small river that comes in below Horseshoe. It's<br/>
called the Leaf gauge,<br/>
http://waterdata.usgs.gov/nwis/uv?cb_00065=on&cb_00045=on&format=gif_default&period=7&site_no=02331000<br/>
I'm not sure of the correlation between the Leaf gauge and the Duncan Bridge gauge. I think the<br/>
Leaf gauge is generally a foot higher. </div>
